=====Usage notes=====
* This suffix is very productive and can be added to almost any word. When the resulting word is not perceived to be a real word, a hyphen is often used before the suffix ({{m|en|sandcastle}} ‚Üí {{m|en||sandcastle-y}}). A few long-established words ending with this suffix have distinctive spellings, such as {{m|en|wintry}} and {{m|en|fiery}}, which English learners might misspell as {{m|en|*wintery}} and {{m|en||*firey}}.

