## {{lb|en|auxiliary}} {{non-gloss definition|A syntactic marker in [[negation]]s with the [[indicative]] and [[imperative]] moods.}}
##: {{ux|en|I '''do''' not go there often.}}
##: {{ux|en|'''Do''' not listen to him.}}
##* {{RQ:Churchill Celebrity|IV|51|‚ÄúWell,‚Äù I answered, at first with uncertainty, then with inspiration, ‚Äúhe would do splendidly to lead your cotillon, if you think of having one.‚Äù &para; ‚ÄúSo you '''do''' not dance, Mr. Crocker?‚Äù &para; I was somewhat set back by her perspicuity.}}
## {{lb|en|auxiliary}} {{non-gloss definition|A syntactic marker for [[emphasis]] with the indicative, imperative, and [[subjunctive]] moods.}}
