##: {{ux|en|'''Do''' tell us.}}
##: {{ux|en|It is important that he '''do''' come see me.}}
##* {{quote-book|en|year=1913|author={{w|Joseph C. Lincoln}}|chapter=7| title=[http://openlibrary.org/works/OL5535161W Mr. Pratt's Patients]| passage=‚ÄúI don't know how you and the ‚Äòhead,‚Äô as you call him, will get on, but I '''do''' know that if you call my duds a ‚Äòlivery‚Äô again there'll be trouble. It's bad enough to go around togged out like a life saver on a drill day, but I can stand that 'cause I'm paid for it. [‚Ä¶]‚Äù}}
## {{lb|en|pro-verb}} {{non-gloss definition|A syntactic marker that [[antecedent|refers back]] to an earlier verb and allows the speaker to avoid repeating the verb; in most dialects, not used with auxiliaries such as {{m-lite|en|be}}, though it can be in [[AAVE]].}}
##: {{ux|en|I '''play''' tennis; she '''does''' too.}}
##: {{q|nonstandard}} {{ux|en|They don't think it '''be''' like it is, but it '''do'''.}}
