|title=[http://www.avclub.com/articles/i-love-lisa,83183/ TV: Review: THE SIMPSONS (CLASSIC): ‚ÄúI Love Lisa‚Äù (season 4, episode 15; originally aired 02/11/1993)]
|passage=Ralph Wiggum is generally employed as a bottomless fount of glorious non sequiturs, but in ‚ÄúI Love Lisa‚Äù he stands in for every oblivious chump who ever deluded himself into thinking that with persistence, determination, and a pure heart he can win the girl of his '''dreams'''.}}
# A [[visionary]] [[scheme]]; a [[wild]] [[conceit]]; an [[idle]] [[fancy]].
#: {{syn|en|vision}}
#: {{ux|en|a '''dream''' of bliss}}
