===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|sculle}}, {{m|enm|scolle}} (also {{m|enm|schulle}}, {{m|enm|scholle}}), probably from {{der|en|non|skalli||bald head, skull}}, itself probably related to {{cog|ang|sƒãealu||husk}}. Compare {{cog|sv|skalle}}, {{cog|no|skalle}}. <ref>http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/skull?s=t</ref>

Alternatively, perhaps from {{der|en|non|skoltr}}, {{m|non|skolptr|t=muzzle, snout}}, akin to {{cog|is|skoltur|t=jaw}}, dialectal {{cog|sv|skult}}, {{m|sv|skulle|t=dome, crown of the head, skull}}, {{cog|dum|scolle}}, {{m|dum|scholle}}, {{cog|gml|scholle}}, {{m|gml|schulle|t=clod, sod}}. Compare also {{noncog|goh|sciula}}, {{m|goh|skiula|t=skull}}.

